  "helpTitle": "Help",
  "helpIntro": "JM Manga is a self-hosted manga reader. Below is a quick guide to the main features.",
  "helpServerTitle": "Connect to a service",
  "helpServerBody": "On the first launch the app tries to reconnect to the last used service. If that fails, you can:\n\n• Add a service manually by entering its host, port and optional token.\n\n• Scan the local network to discover services advertised via mDNS.\n\n• Tap a discovered or saved service to connect.",
  "helpBrowseTitle": "Browse and search",
  "helpBrowseBody": "The Home tab shows featured and recently updated albums. Use the Rankings tab to see popular titles by day, week or month. Tap the search icon to search by title or click a tag on an album detail page to search for that tag.",
  "helpFavoriteTitle": "Favorites",
  "helpFavoriteBody": "Tap the heart on a cover or album detail page to add the album to your favorites. Favorites are tied to your JM account and can be synced across devices. You need to add a JM account in Settings to use favorites.",
  "helpReadTitle": "Reading",
  "helpReadBody": "Tap 'Read Now' on an album detail page or select a chapter from the list. While reading, tap the screen to show the toolbar where you can see your progress, jump chapters and toggle favorite. Reading progress is synced automatically.",
  "helpAccountTitle": "Accounts",
  "helpAccountBody": "Go to Settings > JM Comic Accounts to add or manage JM accounts. The app supports multiple accounts; tap one to switch. Anonymous mode is available but cannot use favorites or the Library.",
  "helpLogTitle": "Troubleshooting",
  "helpLogBody": "If something goes wrong, go to Settings > About > View Logs to see recent requests and errors. You can filter by log level, copy a single log entry, or export the full log to share for debugging."
